// button_frame.su — a θ-PARAMETERIZED clickable BUTTON, rendered whole-frame in ONE
// substrate op per colour channel. The trainable-button demo's render core (queue B1):
// a single parameter vector θ drives a rounded-rectangle button composited over a page
// background, and because every θ component arrives as a per-pixel broadcast BUFFER,
// changing θ never recompiles — the optimizer (B3 ButtonAdam) just changes call arguments.
//
// The button shape is a SQUIRCLE (rounded rectangle) field, all elementwise substrate
// arithmetic (hadamard + add/sub), with NO division (the host passes inverse half-extents
// inv_w, inv_h as parameters, the same inverse-scale trick frame_hero.su uses for `invs`):
//
//   sx = (x - cx) * inv_w                 // normalized x offset from the button centre
//   sy = (y - cy) * inv_h
//   inside = ones - (sx^4 + sy^4)         // ~1 at centre, >0 inside the squircle, <0 outside
//                                         // quartic ⇒ rounded-rectangle (squircle) corners
//
// One channel of the rendered frame composites the page colour and the button fill colour
// by this mask, ALL on the substrate (host only clamps the finished channel to [0,1] for
// display and stacks the three channels — the frame_rgb / hero_channel precedent):
//
//   channel = page*(1 - inside) + fill*inside
//           = page - page*inside + fill*inside
//
// θ axes (each a length-(N·N) broadcast buffer the host builds from a scalar):
//   cx, cy     — button centre (layout)
//   inv_w,inv_h— inverse half-width / half-height (size; larger ⇒ smaller button)
//   page       — page-background colour for this channel
//   fill       — button-fill colour for this channel
// The host calls `button_channel` three times (page/fill = θ's per-channel page_*/fill_*
// weights) to get R, G, B as three whole-frame substrate fields, then stacks them.
function vector button_channel(vector x, vector y, vector ones,
                               vector cx, vector cy, vector inv_w, vector inv_h,
                               vector page, vector fill) {
    vector dx = x - cx;
    vector dy = y - cy;
    vector sx = hadamard(dx, inv_w);
    vector sy = hadamard(dy, inv_h);
    vector sx2 = hadamard(sx, sx);
    vector sy2 = hadamard(sy, sy);
    vector sx4 = hadamard(sx2, sx2);
    vector sy4 = hadamard(sy2, sy2);
    vector inside = ones - (sx4 + sy4);
    return page - hadamard(page, inside) + hadamard(fill, inside);
}

// Self-contained sanity entry: a centred unit-ish button, page=0, fill=1 → centre pixel
// = 0 - 0*1 + 1*1 = 1 (the button is lit at its centre).
function vector main() {
    return button_channel(make_real(0.0), make_real(0.0), make_real(1.0),
                          make_real(0.0), make_real(0.0), make_real(1.0), make_real(1.0),
                          make_real(0.0), make_real(1.0));
}
